Package com.example.telecom.paris.model

Interface MazeModel

public interface MazeModel
Interface providing various methods required for displaying a com.example.telecom.paris.maze in a com.example.telecom.paris.maze editor.

    • getMazeBox

      MazeBoxModel getMazeBox (int rowIndex, int colIndex)
      Returns the com.example.telecom.paris.maze box located at the specified coordinates.
      Parameters:
      rowIndex - The index of the row of required com.example.telecom.paris.maze box. The the index starts at 0 located on the top of the com.example.telecom.paris.maze and must be less than the com.example.telecom.paris.maze's height.
      colIndex - The index of the column of required com.example.telecom.paris.maze box. The the index starts at 0 located on the left of the com.example.telecom.paris.maze and must be less than the com.example.telecom.paris.maze's width.
      Returns:
      The required com.example.telecom.paris.maze box model. null if the specified coordinates are invalid.
